Tonsley Innovation District.

Tonsley has several accommodation options to suit a variety of uses, needs and sizes. These options exist across our allotments and tenancies that are available for purchase or lease, or within our two co-working spaces. They are either move-in ready, development-ready or will be available in the future as the Tonsley redevelopment continues to progess.  

Sizes range from 15 square metres to 10,000 square metres and with build heights of varying levels, subject to  Council approval. Accommodation types include office, workshop, manufacturing, display and sales, education and laboratory uses, as well as retail, hospitality and residential. 

Whether you intend to purchase or lease, go big or go small, move-in now or move-in later, enquire today and be part of something bigger. 


Think Together. Thrive Together:
Tonsley is a growing community of progressive and innovative individuals, businesses and institutions that are collectively helping to shape and improve our future.  

As South Australiaâ€™s premier high-value manufacturing destination, located on a 61-hectare site 10km south of the Adelaide CBD, Tonsley Innovation District has been designed to support businesses and organisations to innovate and grow sustainably.
 
This is achieved through the application of the Innovation District Model that provides a unique mix of benefits that are available to all those that choose to thrive together at Tonsley. 

Together at Tonsley:
Tonsley is a melting pot of over 1,700 innovators from more than 35 businesses and 290 co-working members. Add to that some 8,000 students going through the 61-hectare site each year, and there is a lot of activity and innovation within the district. 

Some of the businesses that already call Tonsley home include SAGE Automation, ZEISS, Micro-X, Siemens Energy, Hydrogen Park SA, Tesla, Cushman and Wakefield, Specialised Solutions, AZZO, BAE Systems, Phoenix Contact, Radical Torque Solutions, the Global Centre for Modern Ageing, as well as Flinders University and TAFE SA.  

Find out more about Tonsley Innovation District by visiting our website www.tonsley.com
